<TITLE> Mugger handed over to police </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong May 11 (bdnews24.com)  The public has handed over a mugger to the police after beating him in Agrabad, Chittagong. An auto rickshaw used in mugging was seized and two arms were recovered. The arrested hijacker, Mohammad Yusuf, is now in Chittagong Medical College Hospital. The incident occurred at around 11:30pm on the roadside at Agrabad Bank Colony, said a sub-inspector of the Double Mooring Police Station, Utpal Barua. Yusuf and his three companions tried to hijack Mohammad Absar and his wife as they were in a rickshaw, the police officer told bdnews24.com. Locals came to their rescue, hearing the screams of Absar and his wife, and caught Yusuf. The other three muggers fled the scene, leaving behind the auto rickshaw and two weapons, said Utpal. bdn
